\section submarine_example Arbitrary shape scatterer

It is possible to derive an analytical solution for non-regular shape of scatterer, however, it is insufficient and time consuming.
 If one would like to solve a Exterior Boundary problem with arbitrary shape scatterer, e.g. a submarine.

\subsection sub_marine_input_file Input files
Mesh file with boundary conditions, material properties of sub_marine can be found in helmholtz/meshes/sub_marine.cub,


\subsection execution4 Executing code

\code
mpirun -np 3 ./fe_approximation \
-my_file sub_marine.cub \
-my_is_partitioned false \
-wave_number 5 \
-wave_direction 1,0,0 \
-save_postproc_mesh true \
-ksp_type fgmres -pc_type lu \
-pc_factor_mat_solver_package superlu_dist \
-ksp_monitor -my_order 3 \
-my_max_post_proc_ref_level 1 \
-add_incident_wave true
\endcode

